<br>
          I with a few friends have created a chat channel to keep the gnomes together and having fun. Here's some info . . <br>
<br>
1) Members of &quot;Gnome&quot; MAY be in other guilds naturally.<br>
2) &quot;Gnome&quot; is not a Gnome only organization ; however, in order to be eligable for this you must know the gnomes , be friendly toward them , and be willing to fight for akanon . . . risking your life . If your not a gnome , try to talk to a member of the organization before joining.<br>
3) we are in the process of building right now though we have quite a few regulars. try to invite other gnomes that don't know of &quot;gnome&quot; <br>
4) we will try to have a few events , hunts , perhaps raid with other friendly guilds at a semi regular rate.<br>
5) &quot;gnome&quot; is just a chat channel , NOT a guild . . I like to think of it as more of a organization.<br>
<br>
well there you are if your interested or just simply marvelled simply /join gnome when you are in game.<br>
<br>
I'll try to get a forum up for the Gnome organization.<br>
<br>
Snumpkin Lionheart . . yes . . one Marvellous gnome.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lithwindreaver>Lith Windreaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pervy Gnome Fancier </span><br>  Posts: 217<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/21/03 12:35:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4165.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.inkbard.com/Graphics/newlithsmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Gnomes ! </span><hr size=1> Indeed a fantastic idea! The Gnomes certainly deserve a community like this! I will make sure that all the gnomes I know are aware of this new Gnomish invention! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
